node.title: Chinese city charts highest snowfall since 1905
node.description: It comes amid concerns about keeping homes warm in an area already that was earlier hit by outages.

node.title: PM says there is a light at the end of the tunnel for Aucklanders
node.description: Jacinda Ardern says her brief return home has given her some insight into what Aucklanders have been going through, and she will be coming back to the city "in the not too distant future".

node.title: Anti-Mask School Board Candidate Who Threatened Officials Blames His Election Loss on Fraud
node.description: "We do not comply to your tyranny, whether it be medical tyranny, election integrity, just total tyranny in general," Republican Steve Lynch said in a recent Facebook video.

node.title: US and China unveil co-operation agreement to tackle emissions
node.description: The United States and China have unveiled a deal to ramp up co-operation tackling climate change, including by cutting methane emissions, phasing out coal consumption and protecting forests.

node.title: Cautious welcome for US-China climate agreement
node.description: The world's two biggest CO2 emitters pledge to boost climate co-operation in an unexpected declaration.

node.title: 'Bit of a whirlwind': Black Caps book spot in T20 World Cup final
node.description: The Black Caps are through to the Twenty20 World Cup final in the United Arab Emirates, after a match-winning innings from Daryl Mitchell.
